0) BLUF
- Build an intuitive Gardening system that:
  • Plans beds with companion planting + USDA zone + microclimate.
  • Aligns seed-start/transplant/harvest to Hebrew calendar (month begins at/near full moon); shift off feasts/Sabbath to prep days.
  • Runs irrigation/fertigation schedules (organic recipes), with timers.
  • Logs harvest → Inventory produce[] + Savings ledger + Preservation suggestions and labels.
  • Supports multi-household collaboration to meet shared harvest targets; allocates crops fairly, staggers sowings, resolves conflicts, and syncs calendars.
  • Uses horizontal “raised card” layout (Planner | Tasks | Water/Soil | Harvest/Preservation | Inventory/Savings | Collaboration).

1) One-liners (Job → Output → Next Best Action → Events)
• Plan: “Choose crops & beds → companion map + sow/transplant calendar → ‘Commit Plan’ → garden.plan.committed”
• Start: “Seed-start timeline → tray map + labels → ‘Print labels’ → garden.seed.labels.printed”
• Tasks: “Weekly tasks → checklist + photos → ‘Start Session’ → garden.session.started”
• Water/Soil: “Irrigation & mixes → timers + warnings → ‘Apply’ → garden.irrigation.applied”
• Harvest: “Log harvest → inventory delta + savings update → ‘Confirm’ → harvest.logged”
• Preservation: “Method suggestions → trackers + labels → ‘Log preservation’ → preservation.logged”
• Calendar: “Windows & task blocks (Hebrew-guarded) → ‘Sync’ → calendar.synced”
• Collaboration: “Targets across households → allocations + schedule → ‘Finalize’ → collab.schedule.finalized”

