5) UI acceptance criteria
☐ Planner generates companion map + sow/transplant windows in ≤1s perceived.
☐ Tasks render with tooltips/photos; checklist emits events; “power-hour” works.
☐ Water/Soil applies timers & prints organic recipes; feast/Sabbath guard on automation.
☐ Harvest Confirm updates Inventory + Savings; root cellar toggle logs location/date.
☐ Preservation tracker and label printing per crop.
☐ Calendar sync respects Hebrew rules; suggests prep-day alternates.
☐ Collaboration proposes fair allocations, staggers dates, surfaces conflicts, and syncs calendars.

6) Domain preferences & constraints
- Hebrew calendar: months begin at/near full moon (your rule).
- Feast/Sabbath: shift actions to previous prep day; flag automation that would run during observance.
- Storage goals: % fresh | % canned | % frozen | % dehydrated | % fermented (per crop).
- Predator proofing: fence/gate/trellis warnings; crop-specific notes (e.g., corn+coons).
- Torah diet: meals suggestions omit pork/shellfish.
- Safety: low-acid canning warnings; labels include date/method.

7) Event contract (emit/subscribe)
Emit:
  • garden.plan.committed ({planId})
  • garden.session.started|paused|resumed|completed
  • garden.tasks.updated ({week})
  • garden.irrigation.applied ({scheduleId})
  • harvest.logged ({items, value, ts})
  • preservation.logged ({method, items, ts})
  • calendar.synced ({events})
  • collab.goal.created|updated|deleted
  • collab.allocations.proposed ({allocation, schedule})
  • collab.conflicts.detected ({items})
  • collab.schedule.finalized ({events})
Subscribe:
  • hebrewCalendar.updated → rebuild schedules
  • inventory.low → suggest succession planting
  • weather.updated → adjust irrigation
  • user.prefs.updated → recompute plans

