13) Inventory & Savings flow
1) On harvest Confirm:
   - Create InventoryDelta.produce[]; show human-readable table.
   - Add Savings entry: qty × pricePerUnit; update monthly total.
   - If “Move to root cellar”, set location/date; add log.
   - If preservePlan, open Preservation modal + print labels.
2) Undo path: keep last patchId; allow revert.

14) Companion planting rules (example set)
- Tomato: loves basil, marigold; avoid fennel.
- Brassicas: love dill, chamomile; avoid strawberries.
- Beans: love corn & squash (Three Sisters); may avoid alliums when pest pressure high.
- Carrots: love onions/leeks; avoid dill (late shade).

15) Collaboration (Multi-Household Planning)
Goal
- Coordinate multiple gardeners to hit shared targets (e.g., “120 lb Roma/mo; 30 qt beans/mo; weekly herbs”), with fair allocations & staggered sowings.

New UI
- /garden/collab: <TargetSetter /> | <AllocationBoard /> | <ScheduleAligner /> | <SwapBoard />
- Presence/chat later; start with allocations & schedule.

Agent behaviors
- optimizeAllocations(goal, members, cropFacts): fairness round-robin; sun/bed fit; expectedYield calc; succession every 7/14 days by cadence.
- detectConflicts(schedule, hebrewCal, calendars): mark feast/Sabbath/personal overlaps; suggest shifts (-1 day prep / +2 hours).
- forecastYield(allocation): small sparkline data for UX.
- planCollaborativeGoal(): all-in-one orchestration → emits collab.* + calendar.synced.

Events
- collab.goal.created|updated|deleted
- collab.allocations.proposed
- collab.conflicts.detected
- collab.schedule.finalized

Permissions (later)
- Roles: owner (edit+invite+finalize), editor (edit), viewer (comment).
- Audit trail for goal/alloc/schedule changes.

SwapBoard (later)
- Post surplus/deficit offers; accept → update both inventories; expiry dates.

